article.headline: Princeton 66, Iona 58
article.story: PRINCETON, N.J. (AP) -- Lincoln Gunn had 20 points and six assists -- both game-highs -- as Princeton held off Iona 66-58 on Wednesday. Kyle Koncz added 15 points for the Tigers (2-0), while Zach Finley had 14 points and eight rebounds for Princeton, which hit nearly 45 percent of its shots. Dexter Gray had 18 points and a game-high nine rebounds for Iona (0-2), while Milan Prodanovic had 16 points. Iona did win the battle of the boards, outrebounding Princeton 33-32, but both teams were plagued by sloppy play, as Iona committed 17 turnovers and Princeton had 13. Princeton led for most of the game, but the Gaels rallied in the second half and cut the lead to 49-48 on John Kelly's layup with 9:21 left to play. The Tigers then went on an 8-2 run to regain command.
